=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But what if you don=E2=80=99t already have a SPAC? You=
=E2=80=99re some brilliant financier or operator who wants to get into the =
taking-companies-public business; you would start a SPAC, but you're convin=
ced that the SPARC structure is better. (More investor-friendly, less likel=
y to get you in =E2=80=9940 Act trouble, etc.) The problem you have is givi=
